              <h4 class="modal-title">Priyanka</h4>
              <p>Born and brought up in a small township in Assam, Priyanka grew up in a family which made sure that books were considered the best birthday presents. As such, she fell in love with the Hardy Boys, Malory towers, TinTin and his adventures and Tinkle's stories ever since she got hold of them. One could often find her sitting in the balcony during the school vacations with a book in hand as Simon and Garfunkel played softly in the background. While studying Economics in Lady Shri Ram college for women Priyanka got the opportunity to nurture her pedagogic inclinations by volunteering in a teaching NGO under the National Service Scheme (NSS). As part of the NSS union, she interacted with underprivileged kids of all age groups. These interactions revealed to her their thirst for knowledge and to achieve something in life. Currently a Young India Fellow, Priyanka got an opportunity to meet people in the fellowship who shared her dedication to help the underprivileged and over cups of coffee and excited talks, 'The WordsWorth Project' took shape. Priyanka has a dream to one day see every kid in this country having an equal opportunity to achieve their dream and this project is her first step to make her dream come true.</p>
