              <p>A football enthusiast and a Chemical Engineer from NIT Calicut, Rahul has had no major experience working with kids or books. The journey from a voracious reader during his school days to the occasional reader that he was during his undergraduate studies, is not something which he chose willingly. However, his love for the written word stayed with him throughout his school and college years. The highly stimulating atmosphere at the Young India Fellowship and the ineffable world of literature spun by his friends there have helped revive this love for books in him. He wants to see a world where every kid at least has an opportunity to fall in love with books. This is exactly why The WordsWorth Project is so close to his heart.</p>
            </div>
